extrasystole.definition: a premature systole resulting in a momentary cardiac arrhythmia

extrasystolic.definition: of or relating to or happening during an extrasystole

extraterrestrial.definition: originating or located or occurring outside Earth or its atmosphere

extravagance.definition: the quality of exceeding the appropriate limits of decorum or probability or truth

extravaganza.definition: any lavishly staged or spectacular entertainment

extravasate.definition: force out or cause to escape from a proper vessel or channel

extravasation.definition: an extravasated liquid (blood or lymph or urine); the product of extravasation

extraversion.definition: (psychology) an extroverted disposition; concern with what is outside the self

extreme.definition: of the greatest possible degree or extent or intensity

extremism.definition: any political theory favoring immoderate uncompromising policies

extremist.definition: (used of opinions and actions) far beyond the norm

extremity.definition: an external body part that projects from the body

extremum.definition: the most extreme possible amount or value

extrinsic.definition: not forming an essential part of a thing or arising or originating from the outside

extrospective.definition: not introspective; examining what is outside yourself

extroversive.definition: directed outward; marked by interest in others or concerned with external reality

extrovert.definition: being concerned with the social and physical environment

extroverted.definition: at ease in talking to others

extrude.definition: form or shape by forcing through an opening

extrusive.definition: of rock material; forced out while molten through cracks in the earth's surface

exuberant.definition: produced or growing in extreme abundance

exudate.definition: a substance that oozes out from plant pores

exudation.definition: the process of exuding; the slow escape of liquids from blood vessels through pores or breaks in the cell membranes

exude.definition: release (a liquid) in drops or small quantities

exultant.definition: joyful and proud especially because of triumph or success

exurbia.definition: a residential area outside of a city and beyond suburbia

exuviae.definition: cast-off skins or coverings of various organisms during ecdysis

exuvial.definition: of or relating to the cast-off skins or cuticles of various animals

ezekiel.definition: a Hebrew prophet of the 6th century BC who was exiled to Babylon in 587 BC

ezra.definition: a Jewish priest and scribe sent by the Persian king to restore Jewish law and worship in Jerusalem
